   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>C. God Regarding Man</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>and Being Pleased with Man</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>in the Burnt Offering</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Genesis 4:4 and 8:20-22 speak of the burnt offering, a type of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>God regarded man, that is, respected man, and was pleased with man, not in man's good doing, but in the burnt offering.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>This is why Abel came to offer the burnt offering to God and God regarded both him and his offering.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>D. God Judging the Corrupted World</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>with the Flood</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>and Saving Noah and His Family</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>God judged the corrupted world with the flood and saved Noah and his family through the ark 6:11-20 .</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The ark is another type of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>E. God Judging the Rebellious Man at Babel</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>In the time from God's creation of man to the calling of Abraham, God also judged the rebellious man at Babel, which was the ancient Babylon 11:4-9 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>II.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>FROM THE CALLING OF ABRAHAM</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>TO THE DECREE OF THE LAW THROUGH MOSES</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The second dispensation covers the period of time from the calling of Abraham to the decree of the law through Moses.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The most important aspect of this dispensation was God's promise to Abraham.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>For this reason, Bible teachers calls this dispensation the dispensation of promise.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>A. God Regarding Man in the Burnt Offering</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>As a continuation of the previous dispensation, God again regarded man in the burnt offering 12:7; 13:18; 22:13; 31:54; Job 1:5 .</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>B. God Promising Abraham That in His Seed</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>All the Nations of the Earth Would Be Blessed</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>In addition, God promised Abraham that in his seed, the coming Christ, all the nations of the earth, including us, would be blessed Gen 22:18; Gal 3:8, 16 .</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Eventually this promise was absolutely fulfilled, as revealed in Galatians 3.</S>
   </TEXT>
